If certain mimeType is requested, that shall be returned
Only if a collection of observations needs to be returned and the requested format does not support collections by itself (like O&M 2.0, as of current status - but maybe that will get back in, see Simon Cox's reply), the GetObservationResponse presented here shall be used.
Depends upon O&M 2.0.
FeatureCollection is deprecated in GML 3.2.1
If O&M 1.0 was requested, that shall directly be returned.

GetObservation response:
- Even if observations are made available in multiple offerings (so they may belong to multiple offerings), then the GetObservation response shall not list an observation twice. In other words, no duplicate observations are allowed in a GetObservation response.
